48,http://www.armslist.com/posts/372048,For Sale/Trade:  Thompson 1927 A5 lightweight ~ RARE ~ W/ DRUMS!,"727/813, Tampa/St. Pete, Florida",$ 1,"Listed On: Tuesday, April 17, 2012",Handguns,no type,45 ACP,no type,no type,"Up for grabs is this super rare Thompson A5 light weight. This is was made in West Hurrley New York back in 1975 by Auto Ordinance, this is not a piece of junk Kahr. This has the aluminum receiver, there were 2000 made and that was all and this one has an odd 3 digit serial number. This one features a 13” barrel and foregrip, it is not classified as a AOW as it is over 26” long and has no way to attach a butt stock. If you know anything about these guns you just how rare it is.
This one comes with (6) 32rd stick mags and (2) 50rd Auto Ordinance drums which are rare as well. This also comes with an Auto Ordinance soft bag.
I am firm at $2200 for the setup, this is cheap considering the rarity and the extras. I prefer trades and will consider all reasonable offers.

FTF in the Greater Tampa Bay Area, will ship to buyer's FFL on the buyer's dime. I require a FL DL and CWP. No felons, crazies or anyone else that cannot lawfully own a firearm. Thanks for looking and have a great day!"

368,http://www.armslist.com/posts/372368,For Sale/Trade:  Custom Built Smoker Rig,"Peoria, Peoria, Illinois","$ 2,300","Listed On: Wednesday, April 18, 2012",Miscellaneous,no type,no type,no type,no type,"This is a custom built smoker built from a 300 gallon tank. The smoker is built as a reverse flow smoker. This means there is a heavy solid steel plate running inside the smoking chamber from one end to the other. The side of the firebox is welded tight and there is an opening on the opposite side. The smoke travels under this plate and gets evenly drawn back across the racks for a very even smoke over the whole rack. The plate is also installed with a slight V with a drain coming out the bottom of the tank. The juices will run out of the chamber into a bucket or pan you place on the ground. The firebox is built with a rear opening lid. It can be used to burn charcoal with a custom sized basket or just burn all wood. It works great both ways. Inside the firebox is a custom propane burner that can be used to heat the smoker or start the fires. I used it primarily to start the wood and charcoal, but it will heat the whole smoker as well for times you just need to keep stuff warm. The smoker itself is roughly 66"" long x 36"" wide. Double lids so you don't have to open the whole smoker at one time. Dual exhaust stacks with one lever dampener that controls both stacks. The inside has two full size cooking racks that both slide out for easily tending your smokes and removal for cleaning. The tool box is permanently installed and even comes with a custom made cover for it to help keep the elements out of it. I store everything I need for any smoke in the tool box. But it will be empty when sold. The trailer is built with storage in mind. Plenty of areas for coolers and wood. The LP tanks will not be included. Trailer has lights and a clean title. Its ready to take to any big party and competitions. You will find a lot of friends you didn't know you had with this. I am selling this because I just want to build another one.
I can send additional pics if needed."

My name is Scott Giesick and I am organizing a set of Firearms Classes with Mike Seeklander in Missoula in June that I thought you might be interested in.  A brief summary of the classes and the schedule are listed below.  Mike is handling all the registration and payment on his website:  www.shooting-performance.com .  You can call me at REDACTED if you have any questions.
Mike Seeklander Bio –

Mr. Seeklander is currently employed as the Director of Training at the United States Shooting Academy. He is a federally certified instructor, curriculum developer, and adjunct instructor and has extensive experience teaching firearms, combatives, tactics, and control tactics. Previously, Mr. Seeklander was a Senior Instructor at the Federal Law Enforcement Training Center in Charleston, S.C. Prior to that Mr. Seeklander served as the Branch Chief and Lead Instructor for the Federal Air Marshal firearms division, as well as instructing in the tactics and physical training divisions at the Federal Air Marshal training center in Atlantic City, N.J. Mr. Seeklander was responsible for the development, implementation and supervision of all firearms and tactical shoot-house instruction for the Federal Air Marshal service basic training. In addition, Mr. Seeklander was credentialed as a Federal Air Marshal, providing counter-terrorism security to commercial American air carriers nationwide.
Mr. Seeklander is a combat veteran of Desert Shield and Desert Storm, with five years of active duty and four years of reserve duty in the U.S. Marine Corps.

From 1995-98, Mr. Seeklander was employed by the Knox County (TN) Sheriff’s Department’s Corrections division and was a member of its highly trained Special Operations Response Team. From 1998-2001, Mr. Seeklander worked as a police officer for the Knoxville (TN) Police Department where I was assigned as a patrol officer and also as an investigator for the Organized Crime section, investigating narcotics and vice-related crimes at the local, state and federal levels.
In addition to developing curriculum for federal agencies, Mr. Seeklander is a published author with two books and one DVD on the market, and will soon be releasing a third.
Courses
Course: Your Competition Handgun Training Program   Course Length: 2 days
Course Cost: $395.00

Course Description: Your Competition Handgun Training Program is a two day course that reinforces the concepts in his book, which is a complete practical handgun training program (299 pages of drills and information). The program will take your shooting to the next level. The book and subsequent range sessions contain mental, physical, shooting, vision, and planning skills, and then combines them in a three-phase program. This course is ideal for shooting athletes that are newer to the sport and looking for a solid foundation, as well as season shooters looking to gain that competitive edge.
Course Name: Advanced Competition Handgun Training Program     Course Length: 1 days
Course Cost: $195

(Pre-requisites: Students must be graduates of Your Competition Handgun Training Program . Exceptions for high classified shooters are granted in some rare cases, email Mike Seeklander for an exception.

Course Description: Advanced Competition Handgun Training Program is a two day course that expands on the material taught in the first course. The course covers all advanced movement principles and more. The technical stuff that the top shooters know will be taught and honed in this course.
Course Name: Your Defensive Handgun Training Program     Course Length: 2 days
Course Cost: $395.00

Course Description: Your Tactical Handgun Training Program is a complete tactical handgun training program designed to teach you how to train for combative purposes with a handgun as your primary weapon.  The program focuses not only on the execution of skills but in the process to properly train those skills and subsequently improve your results. Self defense context is also thoroughly covered in this program, defining the distance related concepts of a fight with a handgun. This course is ideal for anyone who carries’s a handgun for combative (self defense) purposes, and will benefit both the novice as well as experienced shooters.
Course Name: Your Defensive Rifle Training Program     Course Length: 2 days
Course Cost: $395.00

Course Description: Your Tactical Rifle Training Program is a complete tactical rifle training program designed to teach you how to train for combative purposes with a rifle as your primary weapon. The program will take your rifle shooting to the next level. It is a medium range course designed for those who will employ a rifle a close to medium ranges (10-100 yards). The program is like nothing else available today, focusing in not only the execution of skills but in the process to properly train those skills and subsequently improve your results.

June 10, 2012 – Mike will shoot a local match (Big Sky Practical Shooting club) with some class members from the June 7, 8 & 9 classes.
June 14 & 15, 2012 – Tactical Pistol
June 16 & 17, 2012 – Tactical Rifle
The two day classes are $395 + ammo and the one day class is $195 + ammo

Visa, MasterCard, Discover credit cards accepted with no additional fees. Payment can be made through the auction sites shopping cart, if available. If not, we will send a link to our website's Auction/classified Listing Payment link, so that you can make a secure credit card payment.
NO ADDITIONAL FEES for credit card payments. In fact, we encourage it because it is safer and more secure for all parties involved
Ohio residents will be charged 7.0% sales tax
Transactions requiring FFL's
Please have your FFL dealer fax or email a signed, legible copy within 5 days of the purchase to us
Make sure the FFL holder includes your name on the fax or email
We will include a copy of our FFL with the shipment
Shipping
We will ship handguns via USPS Priority mail, other items may vary
Shipping rates and free shipping offers are for the contiguous 48 states. Additional fees for Alaska and Hawaii
All shipments of firearms will be insured and tracking number will be provided
Shipping fee for handguns will be $20, other items will be marked individually
Will not ship to MD, NY, Washington DC
It is the buyer's responsibility to make sure the item purchased is legal in their area
We WILL ship to CA if the item is on the approved list and meets the state's requirements. Shipping times may increase by a couple days due to the additional paperwork required.
Warranties/Returns
New firearms carry the warranty from the manufacturer
Used firearms are sold As Is
If for some reason you believe the item you received is not as we represented, please contact us. We want you to be happy with your purchase!
Trades
We do not routinely accept trades, but on rare occasions we will consider them
Terms will be worked out through email/phone prior to any shipments

Once terms are agreed upon by both parties, we will send a copy of our FFL to your licensed dealer. Your dealer will ship your firearm to us. Once we receive your firearm, we will then ship the agreed upon product to your FFL dealer.
Questions
We strongly encourage you to contact us at if you have any questions regarding an item you may wish to purchase. We want to make sure you have confidence in your purchase.
Our products are also for sale locally and we reserve the right to end the sale/auction early as long as there are no bids over any set reserve price.
New gun listings may use stock photos. Serial numbers in pictures may not be the same as the gun shipped."
